    <description>Homura - C# ORM</description>
    <releaseNotes>
v14.1.0: Major read-path overhaul. Generated and non-generated DAOs now both reach Dapper-class throughput.

New APIs (Source Generator emits these on entities with primary keys):
- Task&lt;E&gt; FindByPrimaryKeyAsync(pk..., conn, timeout) — strongly-typed positional args, const SQL, no Dictionary allocation
- Task&lt;int&gt; DeleteByPrimaryKeyAsync(pk..., conn, timeout) — same pattern for deletes

Source Generator additions:
- SELECT fast path: const SQL template plus a ToEntityFast override using literal ordinals and typed reader.GetXxx calls (skips SafeGet wrapping)
- FindBy / Delete fast path: per-DAO ConcurrentDictionary cache of SQL keyed by the sorted key set; the Dictionary entry point routes through it before the QueryBuilder fallback
- DeleteAll const SQL

Core runtime improvements:
- Dao&lt;E&gt;.Table now caches the Table&lt;E&gt; instance; EntityVersionType setter invalidates the cache
- EntityReaderCache&lt;E&gt; compiles a per-(type, version) Func&lt;IDataRecord, ITable, E&gt; via Expression trees, replacing the per-row reflection loop (DelegateCache lookups, GetInterfaces probes, CatchThrow closures) in ToEntityInDefaultWay
- ConcurrentDictionary cache for Type.GetType(assemblyQualifiedName); SafeGetType also fixes a latent DBNull bug
- QueryBuilder switches Relay from per-step List copy to a lazily-materialized parent-pointer chain; Merge replaces builder.ToString() per iteration with HasContent + LastCharIsSpace flags and caches Represent() per call
- s_logger is a static readonly Logger field; Debug calls that build parameter strings are now guarded by IsDebugEnabled
- OverridedColumns.Count replaces null-check + LINQ Any() in every fast-path guard

Public surface:
- IColumn gains a PropertyInfo accessor (used by the compiled reader). External implementations of IColumn need to add it.
- Dao&lt;E&gt;.s_logger visibility changed from private to protected so generated subclasses can guard their Debug calls.

Benchmark highlights (AMD Ryzen 9 5950X, SQLite, .NET 9):
- Select 1000 rows, non-generated DAO: 11.6 ms / 5.9 MB -&gt; 2.6 ms / 557 KB
- Select 1000 rows, generated DAO: 2.4 ms / 836 KB -&gt; 1.8 ms / 436 KB (matches Dapper)
- FindBy 1000 PK lookups, Typed PK: 158 ms / 2316 KB (beats Dapper at 159 ms / 2495 KB on both axes)

All 197 existing tests pass plus 3 new TypeCacheTest cases.
    </releaseNotes>
